WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.660
CHRISTINE BREINER: Welcome
to recitation.

00:00:08.660 --> 00:00:12.500
Today what I'd like us to do
is look at the inequality

00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:15.630
tangent x bigger than x for
the x values between

00:00:15.630 --> 00:00:16.570
0 and pi over 2.

00:00:16.570 --> 00:00:20.850
We want to show that that is
definitely true using the mean

00:00:20.850 --> 00:00:21.960
value theorem.

00:00:21.960 --> 00:00:24.080
And I want to point out that
this was actually something

00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:26.760
that Joel used when he was
a graphing tangent x and

00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:30.580
arctangent x on the
same x, y plane.

00:00:30.580 --> 00:00:35.220
He used this fact in order to
get the right-looking graph.

00:00:35.220 --> 00:00:37.680
So what I'd like you to do,
again, is I want you to show

00:00:37.680 --> 00:00:40.690
that for any x between 0 and
pi over 2, tangent x

00:00:40.690 --> 00:00:41.880
is bigger than x.

00:00:41.880 --> 00:00:43.620
And use the mean value
theorem to do it.

00:00:43.620 --> 00:00:45.980
I'll give you a little time to
think about it, to work on it,

00:00:45.980 --> 00:00:47.580
and then I'll be back and
we'll do it together.

00:00:56.330 --> 00:00:56.580
OK.

00:00:56.580 --> 00:00:57.790
Welcome back.

00:00:57.790 --> 00:00:59.070
So I'm going to take us through

00:00:59.070 --> 00:01:00.400
how to do this problem.

00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:02.760
And what I want to do is
I want to point out

00:01:02.760 --> 00:01:03.900
a few things initially.

00:01:03.900 --> 00:01:06.630
So what I'm going to do is I'm
going to remind us of the form

00:01:06.630 --> 00:01:08.590
of the mean value theorem
that we need.

00:01:08.590 --> 00:01:16.060
And the form that we need will
be f of x is equal to f of a

00:01:16.060 --> 00:01:20.610
plus f prime of c
times x minus a.

00:01:20.610 --> 00:01:29.420
And here, remember, c has
to be between a and x.

00:01:29.420 --> 00:01:35.230
So in this case, what we want to
consider is the region from

00:01:35.230 --> 00:01:37.360
0 up to some x value.

00:01:37.360 --> 00:01:40.490
So always, this is, if you think
about it, the a and the

00:01:40.490 --> 00:01:44.420
x, well, a will be 0 and x will
be the right hand region,

00:01:44.420 --> 00:01:46.280
always less than pi over 2.

00:01:46.280 --> 00:01:49.790
So what we need to check is, I'm
going to consider f of x

00:01:49.790 --> 00:01:52.730
equal tangent x.

00:01:52.730 --> 00:01:57.870
And what I need to consider is,
does tangent x satisfy the

00:01:57.870 --> 00:01:59.910
hypotheses of the mean
value theorem on

00:01:59.910 --> 00:02:01.230
the region of interest?

00:02:01.230 --> 00:02:05.600
And so our region of interest
will always be a equals 0 and

00:02:05.600 --> 00:02:10.390
b is equals to x, which is
less than some pi over 2.

00:02:10.390 --> 00:02:14.270
And it is true, tangent x is
continuous between 0 and any

00:02:14.270 --> 00:02:15.860
value less than pi over 2.

00:02:15.860 --> 00:02:19.910
And it's also differentiable
between 0 and any value less

00:02:19.910 --> 00:02:20.910
than pi over 2.

00:02:20.910 --> 00:02:24.670
So I can apply the mean value
theorem to tangent x.

00:02:24.670 --> 00:02:27.010
So in order to do this now, what
I'd like to see is what

00:02:27.010 --> 00:02:30.650
kind of things I need
for the right hand

00:02:30.650 --> 00:02:32.520
side of this equation.

00:02:32.520 --> 00:02:35.260
So I obviously need to know what
the output is at a, which

00:02:35.260 --> 00:02:36.795
is equal to 0.

00:02:36.795 --> 00:02:38.990
So let's recall f of 0.

00:02:38.990 --> 00:02:41.870
Well, tangent 0 is 0-- it's
sine of 0 divided

00:02:41.870 --> 00:02:43.500
by cosine of 0.

00:02:43.500 --> 00:02:47.500
And then I need to evaluate
the derivative somewhere

00:02:47.500 --> 00:02:52.120
between a, which is
0, and pi over 2.

00:02:52.120 --> 00:02:53.760
x can be any value less
than pi over 2.

00:02:53.760 --> 00:02:57.940
So let's evaluate what the
derivative is in terms of x.

00:02:57.940 --> 00:02:59.880
We did this, actually, in
another recitation.

00:02:59.880 --> 00:03:04.890
The derivative of tangent
x is secant squared x.

00:03:04.890 --> 00:03:08.970
And so now let's plug in what we
know and then see what else

00:03:08.970 --> 00:03:11.785
we need to do in order to finish
solving this problem.

00:03:16.230 --> 00:03:16.890
OK.

00:03:16.890 --> 00:03:20.170
So what we have. f of x, I'm
actually going to write

00:03:20.170 --> 00:03:23.380
tangent x, so we can see
what's happening here.

00:03:23.380 --> 00:03:28.260
f of x is tangent x, and then I
have that that equals, well,

00:03:28.260 --> 00:03:34.650
f of a is 0 plus f prime
evaluated at c--

00:03:34.650 --> 00:03:36.495
so that's going to be
secant squared c--

00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:42.090
times x minus a.

00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:46.520
Well, a here is 0, so this
is just times x.

00:03:46.520 --> 00:03:48.480
So we're very close.

00:03:48.480 --> 00:03:50.210
We're very close to showing
tangent x is

00:03:50.210 --> 00:03:51.460
always bigger than x.

00:03:53.880 --> 00:03:54.030
In fact, you can see
very easily what

00:03:54.030 --> 00:03:55.440
ultimately we need to show.

00:03:55.440 --> 00:03:59.120
We just need to show that secant
squared c is bigger

00:03:59.120 --> 00:04:01.280
than 1 in our region of
interest. And that would do

00:04:01.280 --> 00:04:04.810
it, because then this would
be bigger than 1 times x.

00:04:04.810 --> 00:04:05.651
The right hand side would be
bigger than 1 times x, so that

00:04:05.651 --> 00:04:08.170
would be sufficient

00:04:08.170 --> 00:04:10.610
So let's make sure we understand
what secant squared

00:04:10.610 --> 00:04:12.180
c can look like.

00:04:12.180 --> 00:04:14.530
Or what the values can be.

00:04:14.530 --> 00:04:20.060
So we have c is between
0 and x, which is less

00:04:20.060 --> 00:04:20.685
than pi over 2.

00:04:20.685 --> 00:04:22.430
Right?

00:04:22.430 --> 00:04:23.350
That's where c is.

00:04:23.350 --> 00:04:26.560
So we always need to remember
what values c could possibly

00:04:26.560 --> 00:04:27.910
have.

00:04:27.910 --> 00:04:30.270
And then let's think about
what we know about

00:04:30.270 --> 00:04:31.650
secant of c, there.

00:04:31.650 --> 00:04:39.400
Well, secant of c is equal
to 1 over cosine of c.

00:04:39.400 --> 00:04:42.110
So if you can't remember what
secant's values are, think

00:04:42.110 --> 00:04:44.680
about the values of cosine
in that region.

00:04:44.680 --> 00:04:47.490
So I'm going to draw a rough
sketch of the value of cosine

00:04:47.490 --> 00:04:49.050
between 0 and pi over 2.

00:04:52.179 --> 00:04:56.250
The value of cosine does
something like this.

00:04:56.250 --> 00:04:59.040
This is 0, this is pi over 2.

00:04:59.040 --> 00:05:01.070
This is a very rough sketch.

00:05:01.070 --> 00:05:03.310
But this output is 1.

00:05:03.310 --> 00:05:06.820
So between 0 and pi over
2, cosine of c is

00:05:06.820 --> 00:05:08.880
always less than 1.

00:05:08.880 --> 00:05:12.515
So 1 over cosine of c is
always bigger than 1.

00:05:12.515 --> 00:05:14.270
OK?

00:05:14.270 --> 00:05:16.120
Because we're taking that
reciprocal value.

00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:20.660
So again, cosine of c from 0
to pi over 2, not including

00:05:20.660 --> 00:05:22.920
0's, always strictly
less than 1.

00:05:22.920 --> 00:05:25.100
And so 1 over cosine c
is always strictly

00:05:25.100 --> 00:05:26.440
greater than 1.

00:05:26.440 --> 00:05:29.720
And so now I have the
information I need to come

00:05:29.720 --> 00:05:31.260
back and finish the problem.

00:05:31.260 --> 00:05:33.030
So again, we were looking at
the expression, we have

00:05:33.030 --> 00:05:37.930
tangent x is equal to secant
squared c times x.

00:05:37.930 --> 00:05:41.380
Well, now I know secant c is
bigger than 1, so now I know

00:05:41.380 --> 00:05:45.680
this whole thing is bigger than
1 times x, which is just

00:05:45.680 --> 00:05:47.220
equal to x.

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:50.720
So if you noticed, on the left
hand side we have a tangent x

00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:54.860
equals something which
is bigger than x.

00:05:54.860 --> 00:05:58.650
So we've just shown that, for
any value of x between 0 and

00:05:58.650 --> 00:06:03.290
pi over 2, tangent x
is bigger than x.

00:06:03.290 --> 00:06:05.230
And I think we'll stop there.